CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1946, pg. 8, reads: "Completing Plans for Concert - These attractively dressed ladies were busy Sunday afternoon at the Centre Avenue Branch YWCA making final plans for a concert scheduled for Friday, April 26, at A. Leo Weil School. Left to right are Mrs. Charles Waters Jr., Mrs. Morris Gaddie, Mrs. John Alston Jr., Miss Evelyn Robinson, Mrs. Lewis Hendricks and Miss Catherine Berry. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, including Mrs. Charles Waters Jr., Mrs. Morris Gaddie, Mrs. John Alston Jr., Evelyn Robinson, Mrs. Lewis Hendricks, and Catherine Berry, posed around striped sofa in YMCA or YWCA
